# Releasing Mila

This is the canonical release SOP. Follow it whenever the user asks for a new
release ("release v1.2.0", "cut a new version", "ship the latest as v…").

## Versioning

- **SemVer.** `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`.
  - `MAJOR` — incompatible model / file-format changes that break older
    installs without a migration. Bump with care.
  - `MINOR` — new features (new hotkey, new model, new view).
  - `PATCH` — bug fixes, dependency bumps, polish.
- Tags are **always** prefixed with `v`: `v1.0.0`, `v1.2.3`. The release
  workflow looks for `refs/tags/v*.*.*`.
- Internal build pre-1.0 already shipped to internal testers as v1.0.0; first
  external release should bump to **v1.1.0** (MINOR) at the earliest.

## Pre-flight checklist

Before tagging:

- [ ] `main` is green in CI (`gh run list --workflow=CI.yml --branch=main --limit=1`).
- [ ] `make test` passes locally.
- [ ] Version is bumped in **one** place: `project.yml`'s top-level
      `settings.base.MARKETING_VERSION` and `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION`. Both
      `Mila/Resources/Info.plist` and the target's `info.properties`
      block use `$(MARKETING_VERSION)` / `$(CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION)` so they
      inherit automatically — do **not** hardcode literals in either place
      (a stale literal caused v1.2.4 to ship with build 6 instead of 7,
      which then put the Sparkle client into an infinite update loop).
- [ ] `CFBundleVersion` (build number) is monotonically incremented — Sparkle
      keys updates by this value, so a stale build number means existing
      installs won't see the update even when `CFBundleShortVersionString`
      bumps. The release workflow reads `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION` from
      `project.yml` (NOT from `Info.plist`, which still contains the literal
      `$(CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION)` placeholder until xcodebuild interpolates
      it) — keep it that way; reading the unprocessed plist gave us
      `sparkle:version=""` for v1.2.5 and broke the appcast.
- [ ] If the model catalog changed, the size + URL fields in
      `Mila/Transcription/ModelManager.swift` reflect reality.

## Cutting the release

Releases run through the **`mila-sign-and-notarize` Jenkins job** on
`jenkins.island.io` (Island employees only; **requires the Island VPN** — it
cannot be reached or triggered from outside the corp network). The old
tag-driven GitHub Actions `release.yml` has been removed.

**Common first step:** merge the release work to `main` first
(`gh pr merge --squash` or via GitHub), with the version bump
(`MARKETING_VERSION` + `CURRENT_PROJECT_VERSION` in `project.yml`) already in
the merged commits. Tag the release commit so the artifact is traceable:

```bash
git pull origin main
git tag v<NEW_VERSION>
git push origin v<NEW_VERSION>
```

### Run the Jenkins job

From the Jenkins UI (or the Jenkins MCP, only when on the Island VPN), trigger
`mila-sign-and-notarize` with:

- `gitRef` — the tag/branch/SHA to build (e.g. `v<NEW_VERSION>` or `main`)
- `skipNotarize` — `false` for a real release (`true` only for fast sign-only iteration)
- `sharedLibraryRef` — usually leave default

The job builds Release `Mila.app`, signs with the Island Developer ID
identity + hardened runtime, notarizes via `notarytool --wait`, staples, and
archives `Mila-<version>.dmg` as a build artifact.

> **Sparkle auto-update note:** as of now the job does NOT upload the DMG/ZIP
> or update the appcast on the `island-whisper-updates` S3 bucket — so an
> auto-update is not published. Distribution is the archived artifact only.
> Wiring S3 upload into the job requires granting the `mac-builder` IAM
> principal S3 write on `island-whisper-updates` in the infrastructure repo
> (`environments/prod/zero-abstraction/iam/policies/jenkins-worker-policy.json`,
> mirroring infra PR #7888), then adding a publish step (reuse
> `scripts/update-appcast.py` + the Sparkle EdDSA signing the old `release.yml`
> did).

### Fallback: manual local build (no notarization)

```bash
make clean
make dmg                       # produces an ad-hoc-signed Mila-<version>.dmg
```

Ad-hoc DMGs trip Gatekeeper (right-click → Open). Use only when Jenkins is
unavailable and notarization isn't required.

## DMG details

- Built by `scripts/make-dmg.sh` from a Release config build.
- Ad-hoc signed (`codesign -s -`). On first launch macOS shows the standard
  Gatekeeper prompt — **right-click → Open** the first time, or notarize.
- For App Store / external distribution, set `DEVELOPMENT_TEAM` in
  `project.yml`, re-enable `com.apple.security.app-sandbox` in the
  entitlements file, and sign with a Developer ID Application certificate.

## After the release

- Verify the DMG at the release page mounts cleanly and the .app launches.
- Update any internal channel pointing at the latest version.
- For internal-only releases (default for this repo) post the link in the
  team Slack channel.
